TWO people have been shot and killed by unknown suspects while seven others were left injured on Friday, 22 July. The suspects, driving a silver Polo, reportedly fired shots randomly at patrons who were sitting outside a tavern in Ga-Rankuwa, north of Tshwane. READ: Tavern owner, assistant left dead and naked in pool of blood Colonel Dimakatso Sello said the motive for the shooting was unknown, and police would be investigating two cases of murder and seven of attempted murder. “Anyone with information about the incident or suspects is urged to report to their nearest police station, contact Crime Stop at 08600 10111 or leave a tip-off via MySAPS app,” she added.